==English==

===Etymology===
Probably from ''[[w:The Ballad of Chevy Chase|Chevy Chase]]'', the scene of a battle celebrated in a number of early ballads.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/'ʧɛvi/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛvi|-ɛvi]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|chev|ies}}
#A hunt or pursuit.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|chev|i|ed}}

# to [[hunt]] or [[chase]]
#:*'''1893''': On the contrary, it seemed rather a piquant thing to us to '''chevy''' him about the playground and hit him over the shins with a wicket. — Arthur Conan Doyle, ‘The Naval Treaty’ (Norton 2005, p.666)

